                    <h5 class="home-title">How does it work?</h5>
                    <hr>
                    <p class="home-paragraph">
                        There are two ways to use Airmed.
                    </p>
                    <p class="home-paragraph">
                        The first and easiest is to upload a file and share it publicly through the <span class="font-weight-bold">hash address</span> that the system returns. This allows you to download it from any InterPlanetary Filesystem client that is connected to the public network. Files also become available through the <span class="font-weight-bold">IPFS gateway</span>. Just attach the hash address to the IPFS url, as shown below.
                    </p>
                    <h6 class="home-title">Example</h6>
                    <ul>
                        <li class="guide-number">
                            <p class="guide-paragraph">With a file with IPFS hash being</p>
                            <p class="p-word-break guide-paragraph"><span class="font-weight-bold">QmNdWbbe3jsHUUYZwq2w9eCkHD1JefV1oM7m4DkSJF4wzp</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="guide-number">
                            <p class="guide-paragraph">https://gateway.ipfs.io/ipfs/<span class="font-weight-bold">&lt;the hash address goes here&gt;</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="guide-number">
                            <p class="guide-paragraph"><span class="font-weight-bold">Like...</span></p>
                            <p class="p-word-break guide-paragraph"><a href="https://gateway.ipfs.io/ipfs/QmNdWbbe3jsHUUYZwq2w9eCkHD1JefV1oM7m4DkSJF4wzp" target="_blank">https://gateway.ipfs.io/ipfs/QmNdWbbe3jsHUUYZwq2w9eCkHD1JefV1oM7m4DkSJF4wzp</a></p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <p class="home-paragraph">
